# Naming Conventions

## File and Directory Structure Philosophy

We use different naming conventions to visually separate different types of code:

- **PascalCase for Components**: Component folders AND files use PascalCase to make them easily distinguishable
- **camelCase for Component Utilities**: Local helper files within component folders use camelCase
- **kebab-case for Functional Code**: Used for app, data/api, and utils folders outside of components
- **Universal Testing**: All files require matching `.spec.tsx` or `.spec.ts` files (except `*Types.ts` files)

## File and Directory Naming

### Component Files

Components use **PascalCase** for both files and directories:

```
✅ CORRECT Component Structure:
components/
├── AuctionCard/
│   ├── AuctionCard.tsx          # Component file
│   ├── AuctionCard.spec.tsx     # Test file
│   └── AuctionCard.types.ts     # Types file (if needed)
├── UserProfile/
│   ├── UserProfile.tsx
│   └── UserProfile.spec.tsx
└── BidHistoryModal/
    ├── BidHistoryModal.tsx
    └── BidHistoryModal.spec.tsx

// ✅ CORRECT - Named exports in component files
export const UserProfile = ({ userId }: UserProfileProps) => {
    // Component implementation
};

❌ INCORRECT:
components/
├── auction-card/                 # Wrong: kebab-case directory
├── auctionCard/                  # Wrong: camelCase directory
└── Auction-Card/                 # Wrong: mixed case
```

### Non-Component Directories (Functional Code)

Use **kebab-case** for non-component directories:

```
✅ CORRECT Non-Component Directories:
src/
├── hooks/
│   ├── useAuth.ts
│   └── useLocalStorage.ts
├── utils/
│   ├── formatters.ts
│   └── validators.ts
├── data/
│   └── auction/
│       ├── useGetAuctions.ts
│       └── usePostAuction.ts
└── types/
    ├── auction.ts
    └── user.ts

❌ INCORRECT:
src/
├── Hooks/                        # Wrong: PascalCase
├── data-layer/                   # Wrong: kebab-case is correct here
└── UTILS/                        # Wrong: SCREAMING_CASE
```

### Functional Code Folders (App, Data, Utils)

Use **kebab-case** for functional folder structures:

```
✅ CORRECT - Functional folder structure with kebab-case:
app/
├── auction-details/
│   ├── page.tsx
│   └── layout.tsx
├── user-profile/
│   ├── page.tsx
│   └── loading.tsx

data/
├── auction/
│   ├── use-auction-details.ts
│   ├── use-bid-history.ts
│   └── auction-types.ts

utils/
├── date-utils.ts
├── currency-utils.ts
└── validation-utils.ts
```

### Special Next.js Files

Follow Next.js conventions:

```
app/
├── layout.tsx                    # Always lowercase
├── page.tsx                      # Always lowercase
├── loading.tsx                   # Always lowercase
├── error.tsx                     # Always lowercase
└── not-found.tsx                 # Kebab-case for multi-word
```

## Export Patterns

### Named Exports Only

**Always use named exports** (except for Next.js page.tsx files):

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Named export
export const AuctionCard = ({ auction }: AuctionCardProps) => {
    return <div>{auction.title}</div>;
};

// ✅ CORRECT - Multiple named exports
export const formatCurrency = (amount: number) => { /* ... */ };
export const formatDate = (date: Date) => { /* ... */ };

// ❌ AVOID - Default export (except in page.tsx)
export default function AuctionCard() { /* ... */ }
```

### Next.js Page Exception

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Default export ONLY in page.tsx
// app/auctions/page.tsx
export default function AuctionsPage() {
    return <div>Auctions</div>;
}
```

## Variable and Function Naming

### Boolean Variables

Use auxiliary verbs for clarity:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT Boolean Naming
const isLoading = false;
const hasError = true;
const canEdit = checkPermission('edit');
const shouldRefetch = isStale && isVisible;
const willExpire = expiryDate < tomorrow;
const wasUpdated = lastModified > lastViewed;

// ❌ AVOID
const loading = false; // Unclear if boolean
const error = true; // Could be error object
```

### Function Names

Use verb phrases that describe the action:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT Function Naming
const fetchUserData = async (id: string) => { /* ... */ };
const calculateDiscount = (price: number, percent: number) => { /* ... */ };
const validateFormData = (data: FormData) => { /* ... */ };
const handleSubmit = (event: React.FormEvent) => { /* ... */ };

// ❌ AVOID
const userData = async (id: string) => { /* ... */ }; // Not a verb
const discount = (price: number) => { /* ... */ }; // Unclear action
```

### Event Handlers

Prefix with 'handle' or 'on':

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT Event Handler Naming
const handleClick = (event: React.MouseEvent) => { /* ... */ };
const handleSubmit = (data: FormData) => { /* ... */ };
const onSelectionChange = (selected: string[]) => { /* ... */ };

// In props
type ModalProps = {
    onConfirm: () => void;
    onCancel: () => void;
};
```

## Type and Interface Naming

### Type Naming Conventions

```typescript
// Component props - suffix with 'Props'
type AuctionCardProps = {
    auction: Auction;
    onSelect?: (id: string) => void;
};

// API responses - suffix with 'Response'
type GetAuctionsResponse = {
    auctions: Auction[];
    pagination: Pagination;
};

// API requests - suffix with 'Request' or 'Data'
type CreateAuctionRequest = {
    title: string;
    startDate: Date;
};

// Form data - suffix with 'FormData' or 'Form'
type AuctionFormData = {
    title: string;
    description: string;
};

// Domain types - use singular nouns
type Auction = {
    id: string;
    title: string;
    status: AuctionStatus;
};
```

## Constant Naming

Use SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE for true constants:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT Constant Naming
export const API_TIMEOUT = 30000;
export const MAX_FILE_SIZE = 5 * 1024 * 1024; // 5MB
export const DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE = 20;

// For const assertions, use PascalCase
export const AuctionStatus = {
    DRAFT: 'draft',
    PUBLISHED: 'published',
    ACTIVE: 'active',
    CLOSED: 'closed',
} as const;
```

## Summary of Naming Rules

| Context             | Directories   | Files                    | Exports         | Test Files            |
| ------------------- | ------------- | ------------------------ | --------------- | --------------------- |
| **Components**      | `PascalCase/` | `PascalCase.tsx`         | Named exports   | `PascalCase.spec.tsx` |
| **Component Utils** | `PascalCase/` | `camelCase.ts`           | Named exports   | `camelCase.spec.ts`   |
| **App Routes**      | `kebab-case/` | `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx` | Default exports | `page.spec.tsx`       |
| **Data/API**        | `kebab-case/` | `kebab-case.ts`          | Named exports   | `kebab-case.spec.ts`  |
| **Utils**           | `kebab-case/` | `kebab-case.ts`          | Named exports   | `kebab-case.spec.ts`  |
| **Types**           | `kebab-case/` | `kebab-case-types.ts`    | Named exports   | None                  |
